          <note type="abstract" xml:lang="en" corresp="http://syriaca.org/persons http://syriaca.org/johnofephesus http://syriaca.org/johnofephesus/persons">
            <quote source="#bib5099-4">Ino was the wife of Tiberius, but Sophia did not allow her to reside in the imperial palace together with Tiberius when he was Caesar from 574 to 578. After Justin's death in 578, Tiberius elevated her to the rank of Augusta and declared to the people that she would be known as Aelia Anastasia. She moved into the palace, where she remained after her husband's death in 582.</quote>
